      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JACKY LEGS (7) filled a minor placing last start at this track behind Zipping Aladdin (25.29) in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Sure to be about the mark. NANGAR NOAH (4) last appeared when too good (23.01) over 400m at Maitland on December 5. Resumes after finishing sixth (23.01) at Maitland over 400m six-and-a-half months ago. Expected to feature on best form. HEATHERLY LOMAR (2) isn't a quick beginner but comes home hard, finishing out of the frame two back but did wind up strongly to place when second (25.34) in a Grade 5 at Maitland. Won at her only start from this draw. Winning chance. AL'S MEMORY (6) found the frame for the second consecutive time when narrowly beaten into third last time out (26.37) over 472m at Bulli. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a tricky draw.",
